 continuously track the incoming signal and lock is lost (Kamel, Borio et al. 2011). This motivated the use of another GPS signal to aid the main L1 C/A signal. In this paper the possibility of expanding the design of the fuzzy tracking system to include a second GPS frequency particularly L2C signal is explored. System design of possible integrated configurations, test and analysis are introduced. Test results show that using L2C Doppler aiding to the L1 fuzzy tracking loop enables the system to maintain signal lock at high levels of L1 signal interference which was not possible using the classical techniques of the original fuzzy system design.
